Based on the provided context, registered land is defined in the context of private land in Article 64 of the Kenya 2010 Constitution. According to this article, private land consists of:

(a) registered land held by any person under any freehold tenure;

Therefore, registered land is a part of private land. It refers to land that is held by an individual or entity under a freehold title, which is a form of ownership where the land is registered in the owner's name and they have full rights to it.

Based on the provided context, the tenure for registered land under private land, as defined by Article 64, is:

- (a) registered land held by any person under any freehold tenure; or
- (b) land held by any person under leasehold tenure;

