In this context, a 'money bill' is defined in Article 114(3) of the Kenya 2010 Constitution as a Bill that contains provisions dealing with any of the following matters:

(a) taxes;
(b) the imposition of charges on a public fund or the variation or repeal of any of those charges;
(c) the appropriation, receipt, custody, investment or issue of public money;
(d) the raising or guaranteeing of any loan or its repayment; or
(e) matters incidental to any of those matters.

However, it is important to note that "tax", "public money", and "loan" do not include any tax, public money or loan raised by a county, as per Article 114(4).

