llm_answer:
Based on the provided context, the specific disqualifications for a person to be elected as a member of a county assembly are outlined in Article 193(2). A person is disqualified if they:

(a) are a State officer or other public officer, other than a member of the county assembly;
(b) have, at any time within the five years immediately before the date of election, held office as a member of the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission;
(c) have not been a citizen of Kenya for at least the ten years immediately preceding the date of election;
(d) are of unsound mind;
(e) are an undischarged bankrupt;
(f) are serving a sentence of imprisonment of at least six months; or
(g) have been found, in accordance with any law, to have misused or abused a State office or public office or to have contravened Chapter Six.

Based on the provided context, the criteria considered when determining the equitable shares for county governments in Kenya are outlined in Article 203(1) of the Constitution. These criteria are:

(a) the national interest;
(b) any provision that must be made in respect of the public debt and other national obligations;
(c) the needs of the national government, determined by objective criteria;
(d) the need to ensure that county governments are able to perform the functions allocated to them;
(e) the fiscal capacity and efficiency of county governments;
(f) developmental and other needs of counties;
(g) economic disparities within and among counties and the need to remedy them;
(h) the need for affirmative action in respect of disadvantaged areas and groups;
(i) the need for economic optimisation of each county and to provide incentives for each county to optimise its capacity to raise revenue;
(j) the desirability of stable and predictable allocations of revenue; and
(k) the need for flexibility in responding to emergencies and other temporary needs, based on similar objective criteria.

The Commission on Revenue Allocation, as per Article 216, is responsible for making recommendations concerning the basis for the equitable sharing of revenue raised by the national government, taking into account these criteria.

